# A destructuring `for [:x :y] in <expr>` binder lives only within its own loop body: reads of
# `:x`/`:y` inside the body (lines 2-3) resolve cleanly, but a read of `:x` after `end for`
# (line 5) has no visible declaration in scope (spec/grammar.md:127,136-137;
# spec/execution-model.md:317-327).
for [:x :y] in [[1 2] [3 4]]
  print :x
  print :y
end for
print :x
